headline: MetLife Investment Management Announces Driscoll Retirement; Funk Named Interim President
summary: WHIPPANY, N.J., May 02, 2025--MetLife Investment Management (MIM), the institutional asset management business of MetLife, Inc. (NYSE: MET), today announced that after a distinguished career spanning decades in the asset management industry, including eight years at MIM, Jude Driscoll will be retiring from the company, effective May 2. Brian Funk has been appointed as MIM’s interim president.
